-- NTT DoCoMo Plans to Help Sell Phone Applications, Emulate Apple, FT Says
-- Mariko Yasu
-- 2010-07-07T23:20:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/ntt-docomo-to-encourage-phone-applications-emulating-apple-ft-reports.html

          
          
             NTT DoCoMo Inc. plans to loosen
control over software offered to users of its i-mode data
services and help sell applications developed by third-party
providers, the Financial Times reported, citing President Ryuji
Yamada.  
 The changes will make its model similar to that of Apple
Inc., the report said.  
